plum sweet rosé

Plums, commonly known as plums, have a good balance of sweetness and sourness and give the skin a bright ruby color. A sweet wine with a refreshing aftertaste after the fruit and sweetness of ripe plums. We recommend pairing with white meat, sweets and sweets.

Anykščių Vynas

fruit wine winery

Founded in 1926 as a family-owned local winery in the country town of Aniksichei in the northeastern part of Lithuania, "Aniksichu Venus". As a result of focusing on the production of wines using fruits, where grapes do not grow in regions with severe cold, unique brands have become widely loved by Lithuanian people and have grown into the most famous fruit wine winery in the three Baltic countries. bottom.

In 2005, a new wine brand was named "Volta". Voruta is the name of a historic royal castle that is said to have existed around the 13th century in the Anikschei region, where the winery is located.

Lithuania in the 13th century was a state called the Grand Duchy of Lithuania, which dominated the north from the Black Sea and boasted the largest land area in Europe. The name of the castle of King Mindaugas at that time was "Volta", and it is said to be a legendary castle whose exact location is unknown.
